description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic and motivated full time Counselling or Clinical Psychologist to join the Macmillan cancer psychological service in Lewisham and Greenwich NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a three year old, friendly and supportive psychological team. The post holder will have the opportunity to play a role in continuing to shape the service and develop innovative high quality psychological services. The post will involve providing psychological assessment and therapy to patients and their family and carers in the cancer and palliative care services, including virtual sessions, and consultation and training to multi-disciplinary staff within cancer teams. There will be opportunities to be involved in research and audit and to supervise trainees and more junior colleagues. We have strong links with the Dimbleby Care Centre at St Guy’s and Thomas’s NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Clare ReederJob titlePrincipal Clinical Psychologist, Macmillan Psychological Support TeamEmail addressclare.reeder@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
